article.headline: Cleveland State beats Youngstown State 73-60
article.story: CLEVELAND -- Anton Grady netted a double-double, scoring 17 points and grabbing 13 rebounds, to lead Cleveland State to a 73-60 win over Youngstown State on Wednesday night. Charlie Lee added 16 points and three rebounds for the Vikings (14-10, 8-2 Horizon League). Trey Lewis had 10 points and Vinny Zollo had nine. The team sank 43.6 percent from the field overall -- including 8 of 19 from distance -- and 73.9 percent from the free throw line. Cleveland State led 37-28 at the break and continued to outpace Youngstown State in the second half for the win. The Penguins (10-16, 1-10) were 24 of 55 from the field overall, including just 4 of 12 (33.3 percent) from beyond the arc. Shawn Amiker finished with 20 points and 11 rebounds for Youngstown State. Bobby Hain and Osandai Vaughn added 12 points apiece.
